\pard\f0\fs28\b\cf2 12. How to Run\b0\cf1\par
\pard\fs20\par
\pard\fs24\b Backend\b0\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs18 python -m venv venv\par
venv\\Scripts\\activate          # Windows\par
pip install --prefer-binary -r requirements.txt\par
uvicorn src.api.main:app --reload\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par
\pard\fs24\b Frontend\b0\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs18 cd frontend\par
npm install\par
npm run dev\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par
\pard\fs24\b Ollama (LLM)\b0\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs18 ollama pull llama3\par
ollama serve          # starts on http://localhost:11434\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par
\pard\fs24\b PostgreSQL (Docker)\b0\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs18 docker-compose up -d postgres\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par
\pard\fs24\b MLflow UI\b0\par
\pard\li720\f2\fs18 mlflow ui --port 5000          # open http://localhost:5000\par
\pard\f0\fs24\par

{\pard\qc\fs18 ----------------------------------------------------------------\par}

\pard\fs24\par
\pard\f0\fs28\b\cf2 13. Deployment Considerations\b0\cf1\par
\pard\fs20\par
\pard\li720\fs22\bullet The Dockerfile in the project root builds a production image for the FastAPI backend.\par
\bullet docker-compose.yml orchestrates the backend, a PostgreSQL instance, and (optionally) an Ollama container.\par
\bullet For GPU inference, change the DEVICE environment variable to "cuda" and mount the GPU in the Docker run flags.\par
\bullet The secret_key in config.py must be changed to a cryptographically random string before any public deployment.\par
\bullet ALLOWED_ORIGINS must be restricted to the actual domain of the frontend in production (not the wildcard used during development).\par
\pard\fs24\par

{\pard\qc\fs18 ----------------------------------------------------------------\par}

\pard\fs24\par
\pard\f0\fs28\b\cf2 14. Summary\b0\cf1\par
\pard\fs20\par
\pard\fs22 This application is a complete, end-to-end designed system for AI-driven plant disease diagnosis. Every technology choice — FastAPI, PostgreSQL, Ollama, EfficientNet-V2-S, MLflow, Vue 3 — is motivated by real deployment constraints for rural agricultural use. The inference pipeline has a clean fallback chain so the system degrades gracefully when individual components (vision model file, Ollama, database) are unavailable, ensuring the frontend is always accessible. The MLOps layer captures every prediction and the farmer's feedback, creating a continuously growing labelled dataset that can be used to retrain and improve the model over time.\par
\pard\fs20\par
}
